Scheduled Maintenance:
To maintain the security posture of the system, regular maintenance practices were implemented to ensure that all software components, including Kernel-tools, remain up-to-date. This may include setting up automated update schedules or implementing proactive monitoring systems to detect vulnerabilities promptly.
By following these remediation steps, the vulnerability associated with Kernel-tools version 4.14.330-250.540.amzn2.aarch64 was effectively mitigated through the upgrade to the latest version, Kernel-tools 4.14.336-257.568.amzn2.aarch64.


